{
  "texts": [
    "While FL enhances privacy by sharing model updates rather than raw data, there are still vulnerabilities during interactions between FL participants [294].",
    "For instance, adversaries can exploit these vulnerabilities to perform attacks such as membership inference or gradient leakage [294]- [296], aiming to extract local training data from devices.",
    "Existing countermeasures, such as homomorphic encryption (HE) and secure multi-party computation (SMC), while effective in enhancing FL privacy to some extent, fall short in fully addressing these malicious attacks.",
    "As detailed in [297], HE can protect against data leakage but is less effective against more sophisticated threats like membership inference and gradient leakage attacks.",
    "However, it cannot be efficiently applied on large-scale FMs."
  ]
}